ind.Name: Marduk-šumu-ibni
Biography: Protagonist of the Ilia A+B archive. Younger brother of Nabû-bēlšunu and older brother of Nabû-ēṭer-napšāti and Nergal-iddin. Husband of {{f}}Inṣabtu/Marduk-šumu-iddin//Ša-nāšišu. Name: Ardia
ind.Name: Ardia
Biography: This could be an eponym for a place named Bīt-Ardia (maybe a small village in the countryside of Borsippa). Note that "Ardia" is the nickname of Marduk-šumu-ibni/Šulāya//Ilia, the protagonist of the Ilia A+B archive, so it could either referr to a cluster of houses owned by this man, or it could also indicate that he provided an accomodation for the Carians (Waerzeggers 2006a: 7).

Father of Nabû-balassu-iqbi (Nabû-bullissu), {{f}}Amat-Nanāya, {{f}}Amat-Ninlil and {{f}}Binunu. Grandfather of Libluṭ/Nabû-balāssu-iqbi.
